By Kingsley Okoye Abuja – The National Pension Commission (PenCom), has issued licence to the  Nigerian University Pension Management Company Ltd (NUPEMCO) to carry out the business of a Pension Fund Administrator (PFA) in universities. PenCom’s Head of Corporate
Communication, Mr Peter Aghahowa in a statement on Monday in Abuja said
the approval was based on detailed evaluation of NUPEMCO’s compliance
with the requirements stipulated by the Commission. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN)
reports that NUPEMCO was earlier set up to manage the retirement
benefits of staff in Nigerian universities. It has the mandate to improve the post working standards of staff of Nigerian universities. (NAN)